column4:
{
  "category": "Plant-based protein (soy)",
  "typical_unit": "package (often 14–16 oz / 400–450 g) or block",
  "storage_tip": "Unopened tofu: refrigerate in its original packaging and keep submerged in the liquid. Opened tofu: store in a sealed container in fresh water in the fridge and change the water daily; use within ~3–5 days. Freeze only if you want a firmer, chewier texture—thaw in the fridge and drain well.",
  "nutrition_note": "Tofu is a high-protein, soy-based food that’s most distinctive for its ability to take on the flavor of whatever you cook it with."
}

{
  "category": "Spice (saffron threads)",
  "typical_unit": "0.1–0.2 g (small pinch) or 1 g",
  "storage_tip": "Unopened: store in a cool, dark, dry pantry in an airtight container. Opened: keep tightly sealed in an airtight container away from light and moisture to preserve aroma and color.",
  "nutrition_note": "Most distinctive trait: saffron’s powerful floral–honey aroma and deep golden color from its carotenoid compounds. It’s used in very small amounts, so it’s not a major calorie source, but it does provide notable plant antioxidants."
}
